text: The voiced dental lateral fricative is a type of consonant. The letter for this sound in the International Phonetic Alphabet is (ɮ̪) and the equivalent X-SAMPA symbol for this sound is `L_`. This symbol is used to represent the dental click but represents a voiced dental lateral fricative. The voiced dental lateral fricative is distinct from the voiced alveolar lateral fricative. == Sound used in words == Language: English Word: explode IPA: exɮ̪de == Return to == *Voiced alveolar lateral fricative == Lists of co- articulated consonants == == Related pages == *Voiced alveolar lateral fricative Category:Consonants
title: Voiced dental lateral fricative
